UNITED STATES of America, v. R. R. ADAMSON (also Known as Rhoda Rindge Adamson). No. 9398. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 18, 1939. Ben Harrison, U. S. Atty., and Eugene Harpole, Sp. Atty., Bureau of Internal Revenue, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Joseph D. Brady, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above-cause dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
